   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Voice for Victims: 20,000 Documents Expose Crimes</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ahmad* was 15 years old when he was arrested and detained by the Syrian government in 2014 for filming demonstrations, his name listed in SJAC&apos;s collection of government documents from Syria&apos;s security sector. Stories of arbitrary detention have become common in Syria. While we may not know Ahmad&apos;s fate, there are many legal cases of Syrian victims seeking justice. To date, SJAC has 20,000 high-priority documents from the Syrian security sector awaiting analysis, which contain valuable evidence.</narrative>
  </description>
